I was referring the linux code , they have min_rev to differentiate between 3.1 or 3.2 hub , mostly they are reading from the capability register like below 

static void xhci_add_in_port(struct xhci_hcd *xhci, unsigned int num_ports,
		__le32 __iomem *addr, int max_caps)
{
	u32 temp, port_offset, port_count;
	int i;
	u8 major_revision, minor_revision;
	struct xhci_hub *rhub;
	struct device *dev = xhci_to_hcd(xhci)->self.sysdev;
	struct xhci_port_cap *port_cap;

	temp = readl(addr);
	major_revision = XHCI_EXT_PORT_MAJOR(temp);
	minor_revision = XHCI_EXT_PORT_MINOR(temp);

#define	XHCI_EXT_PORT_MAJOR(x)	(((x) >> 24) & 0xff)
#define	XHCI_EXT_PORT_MINOR(x)	(((x) >> 16) & 0xff)

Wanted to know if similarly we can read the capability register from xhci-pci.c
